      "sentence_id": 6423,
      "text": "The opium \nconcern continued under the direction of the Board of Revenue till the beginning of the year 1793, when \nit was transferred to the Board of Trade, and regulations were passed respecting the terms of the contract \nfor the provision of opium in Bengal, Bahar, and Orixa, which was extended for four years, from September \nthe 1st, 1793, to the 31st of August, 1797, also respecting measures for the protection of the cultivators of \nthe poppy, and for preventing illicit trade in the article.",
